                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.AD1/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-30T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >March 30, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. Department’s 168, March 24, 10 p.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d739fn15">See
                        footnote 10, <ref target="#pg_824">p. 824</ref>.</note> In a note dated
                    March 29, Molotov states that the Soviet Government does not object to the
                    inclusion of representatives of the Governments of Iceland, Iran, Liberia, and
                    Egypt among those to be invited to the conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
